<title>UK: UK govt gives green light to first health PFI plan.</title>
<headline>UK govt gives green light to first health PFI plan.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>The UK Department of Health has given the go-ahead to Britain's first private finance initiative health project -- a 280 million stg hospital development in east London.</p>
<p>The project, comprising a new 210 million stg hospital and a 70 million stg medical school, will replace four existing hospitals and lead to 1,000 redundancies over the next four years, the local National Health Service trust said.</p>
<p>The project will carried out by the Health Management Group, a joint venture between contractor AMEC and facility operator Building and Property. The contract will span 30 years.</p>
<p>--London newsroom +44 171 5427717</p>
